comments.text:
I am here to light the flame which reforms the Indian Judicial System in favour of gender neutral laws. Women are not second class citizens, they must enjoy the same privileges that men enjoy and must also be subject to the same laws that apply. The statue of justice has lost it's blindfold, yet gender is taken into consideration when meting out sentences. Mr. Subhash's case is a classic example of the plight of the thousands of men who are currently suffering at the hands of conniving in-laws, an apathetic judiciary and biased laws. Justice must be fairly delivered to all regardless of gender. 
Justice is due - Atul Subhash
